<!-- ───────── ABOUT ───────── -->
<section class="about" id="about">
  <div>
    <div class="section-eyebrow">About Me</div>
    <h2>I left India a decade ago — and never stopped <em>navigating borders</em>.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="about-text">
    <p>Since I left home, I've been juggling savings in multiple currencies, watching a tech career compound across continents, and answering the same question every visa renewal: "where exactly is home?"</p>
    <p>Along the way I learned that most professional advice is built for people who stay still. Single country. Single currency. Single career arc. International life doesn't work that way — and the gap in good education for people like us is enormous.</p>
    <p>So I built my own frameworks for the three areas that matter most: how to save and invest when your money lives across borders, how to design a career that travels with you, and how to navigate the visa, residency and identity questions that come with all of it.</p>
    <p><strong>This is education, not advice.</strong> I won't tell you what to do. I'll teach you how to think — so you can ask better questions of the licensed advisors who eventually do.</p>
    <p><a href="#transparency" class="link">Read my transparency note →</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

